{
  "abstract": "Hardpan A soil layer with physical characteristics that limit root penetration and restrict water movement.\r\nSoil crust A transient soil-surface layer, ranging in thickness from a few millimeters to a few centimeters,\r\nthat is either denser, structurally different or more cemented than the material immediately beneath it,\r\nresulting in greater soil strength when dry as measured by penetration resistance or other indices of soil\r\nstrength.",
